\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Reliability diagrams for Temperature Scaling (TS) and Thermodynamic Entropy Calibration (TEC) on (a) QNLI, where TEC outperforms TS, and (b) SST-2, where TS outperforms TEC. A perfectly calibrated model falls on the diagonal line (dashed). TEC's reliability curve is closer to the diagonal on QNLI, while TS is better on SST-2.}}{10}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:reliability}{{4}{10}{Reliability diagrams for Temperature Scaling (TS) and Thermodynamic Entropy Calibration (TEC) on (a) QNLI, where TEC outperforms TS, and (b) SST-2, where TS outperforms TEC. A perfectly calibrated model falls on the diagonal line (dashed). TEC's reliability curve is closer to the diagonal on QNLI, while TS is better on SST-2}{figure.4}{}}
